text: Kutluguza () is a Russian village) in Belsky Selsoviet, Gafuriysky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 314 as of 2010. There are nine streets. == Geography == It is located 22 km from Krasnousolsky, 4 km from Inzelga. == References == Category:Rural localities in Gafuriysky District
title: Kutluguza
